# Jekyll Template Patterns

## Layout Structure

- [site/\_layouts/default.html](mdc:site/_layouts/default.html) is the main template
- Use Liquid templating syntax: `{{ variable }}` and `{% tag %}`
- Include reusable components with `{% include filename.html %}`

## Asset Management

- CSS files are in [site/assets/css/](mdc:site/assets/css/)
- Logo images are in [site/assets/logos/](mdc:site/assets/logos/)
- Icons are in [site/assets/icons/](mdc:site/assets/icons/)
- Reference assets with `{{ site.url }}/assets/...`

## Data Access

- Community data is available via `site.data.output`
- Access future events with `site.data.output.future`
- Access past events with `site.data.output.past`
- Each event has: name, location, tags, members, date, event (link)

## Meta Tags

- Use `{{ page.title | default: site.title | escape }}` for dynamic titles
- Use `{{ page.description | default: site.description | escape }}` for descriptions
- Always escape user content with the `escape` filter

## Styling

- Uses Tabler CSS framework
- Dark theme by default: `class="theme-dark-auto"`
- Custom CSS in `<style>` tags within the layout
  description:
  globs:
  alwaysApply: false

